File-RoundRobin

This module implements a round-robin file. When created, the maximum file size can be specified. 
When you write into the Round-Robin file, if we filled the maximum allowed space we will write over the old data, while always preserving the most recent data.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc File::RoundRobin

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=File-RoundRobin

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/File-RoundRobin

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/File-RoundRobin

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/File-RoundRobin/


